🧠 Offline AI Changelog Assistant

A 100% offline, Python-based changelog documentation assistant powered by a local LLM and Git integration.

📌 Project Goal

Build an offline, privacy-focused documentation assistant that:

Analyzes local software project files

Detects code changes via Git

Uses a local LLM to generate “What’s New” documentation in a user-defined format

Provides a simple web interface for seamless interaction

🚀 Core Features
🔒 100% Offline

Runs entirely on your local machine — no internet connection required.

🌐 Simple Web Interface

A clean browser-based UI built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

🐍 Python Backend

Handles all backend logic, Git operations, and LLM inference using Flask or FastAPI.

📁 Local File System Access

Reads and analyzes your local project directory.

🧬 Git Integration

Parses project history using git diff to identify precise code changes.

🧠 Local LLM Inference

Uses a GGUF model (e.g., mistral-7b.gguf) via llama-cpp-python for on-device text generation.

🧩 System Architecture

A simple client-server architecture, running fully on your local system.

🖥️ Component 1: Frontend (Web UI)

Description: A single-page HTML + JavaScript interface

Functionality:

Displays user inputs and “Generate” button

Sends fetch requests to the backend

Displays AI-generated documentation

⚙️ Component 2: Backend (Python Server)

Framework: Flask / FastAPI

Responsibilities:

Serves the index.html file

Exposes /api/generate_docs endpoint

Uses os, pathlib, and GitPython to analyze codebase

Runs git diff to extract code changes

Formats data into structured AI prompts

Calls the local LLM for text generation

Returns the generated documentation to the frontend

🧠 Component 3: Model (LLM Loader)

Library: llama-cpp-python

Model File: e.g., mistral-7b-instruct.Q4_K_M.gguf

Functionality:

Loads the model from local storage

Performs inference via CPU or GPU

Returns generated text to the backend

🛠️ Technology Stack
Layer	Technology	Purpose
Backend Server	Flask / FastAPI	API & server logic
LLM Inference	llama-cpp-python	Local model inference
Git Interface	GitPython	Fetch Git diffs & commits
Frontend	HTML5, CSS3, JS (ES6+)	User interface
Model Format	GGUF	Optimized local model format

Recommended Model:

🧩 Mistral-7B-Instruct.Q4_K_M.gguf (Best balance of speed & intelligence)

🔮 Future Option: Larger Llama or Mistral 8B+ variants

🧱 Development & Setup Plan
Phase 1: Environment Setup
# Create project folder
mkdir ai_assistant && cd ai_assistant

# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies
pip install flask llama-cpp-python GitPython


Download Model:

Visit Hugging Face

Search for “Mistral 7B Instruct GGUF”

Download a quantized model (e.g., Q4_K_M or Q5_K_M)

Save it inside your ai_assistant folder

Phase 2: Build the Backend (app.py)
# app.py
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify, send_from_directory
from llama_cpp import Llama
from git import Repo
import os

app = Flask(__name__)
llm = Llama(model_path="mistral-7b-instruct.Q4_K_M.gguf")

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return send_from_directory(".", "index.html")

@app.route("/api/generate_docs", methods=["POST"])
def generate_docs():
    data = request.json
    project_path = data.get("project_path")
    repo = Repo(project_path)
    diff_text = repo.git.diff()
    prompt = f"Generate changelog for these changes:\n{diff_text}"
    result = llm.create_completion(prompt)
    return jsonify({"output": result["choices"][0]["text"]})

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)

Phase 3: Build the Frontend (index.html)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Offline AI Changelog Assistant</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>🧠 Offline AI Changelog Assistant</h1>
  <input type="text" id="path" placeholder="Enter Project Folder Path"><br><br>
  <textarea id="prompt" rows="5" cols="60" placeholder="Custom Prompt / Format (optional)"></textarea><br><br>
  <button id="generate">Generate Documentation</button>
  <pre id="output"></pre>

  <script>
    document.getElementById('generate').onclick = async () => {
      const path = document.getElementById('path').value;
      const prompt = document.getElementById('prompt').value;
      const res = await fetch('/api/generate_docs', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
        body: JSON.stringify({project_path: path, custom_prompt: prompt})
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      document.getElementById('output').textContent = data.output;
    };
  </script>
</body>
</html>

Phase 4: Run the Application
python app.py


Then open your browser and visit:
👉 http://localhost:5000

